obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (1468)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1468&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Insecticides Act, 1968.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different States and for different`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st March, 1971, vide notification No. G.S.R. 300, dated 27th February, 1971, in respect of ss. 4, 7, 8 and 36, see Gazette of`
  line `India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `1st August, 1971, vide notification No. G.S.R. 1108, dated the 28th July, 1971, in respect of remaining provisions see Gazette of`
  line `India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (1469)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Application of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1469&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in addition to, and not`
  line `in derogation of, any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (1470)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1470&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "animals" means animals useful to human beings and includes fish and fowl, and such kinds`
  line `of wild life as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify, being`
  line `kinds which, in its opinions, it is desirable to protect or preserve;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Central Insecticides Board constituted under section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) "Central Insecticides Laboratory" means the Central Insecticides Laboratory established or as`
  line `the case may be, the Institution specified, under section 16;`
  line
  line `(d) "import" means bringing into any place within the territories to which this Act extends from a`
  line `place outside those territories;`
  line
  line `(e) "insecticide" means--`
  line
  line `(i) any substance specified in the Schedule; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such other substances (including fungicides and weedicides) as the Central Government`
  line `may, after consultation with the Board, by notification in the Official Gazette, include in the`
  line `Schedule from time to time; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any preparation containing any one or more of such substances;`
  line
  line `(f) "Insecticide Analyst" means an Insecticide Analyst appointed under section 19;`
  line
  line `(g) "Insecticide Inspector" means an Insecticide Inspector appointed under section 20;`
  line
  line `(h) "label" means any written, printed or graphic matter on the immediate package and on every`
  line `other covering in which the package is placed or packed and includes any written, printed or graphic`
  line `matter accompanying the insecticide;`
  line
  line `(i) "licensing officer" means a licensing officer appointed under section 12;`
  line
  line `(j) "manufacture", in relation to any insecticide, includes--`
  line
  line `(i) any process or part of a process for making, altering, finishing, packing, labelling,`
  line `breaking up or otherwise treating or adopting any insecticide with a view to its sale, distribution`
  line `or use but does not include the packing or breaking up of any insecticide in the ordinary course of`
  line `retail business; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any process by which a preparation containing an insecticide is formulated;`
  line
  line `(k) "misbranded"--an insecticide shall be deemed to be misbranded--`
  line
  line `(i) if its label contains any statement, design or graphic representation relating thereto which`
  line `is false or misleading in any material particular, or if its package is otherwise deceptive in respect`
  line `of its contents; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if it is an imitation of, or is sold under the name of, another insecticide; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if its label does not contain a warning or caution which may be necessary and sufficient,`
  line `if complied with, to prevent risk to human beings or animals; or`
  line
  line `(iv) if any word, statement or other information required by or under this Act to appear on the`
  line `label is not displayed thereon in such conspicuous manner as the other words, statements, designs`
  line `or graphic matter have been displayed on the label and in such terms as to render it likely to be`
  line `read and understood by any ordinary individual under customary conditions of purchase and`
  line `use; or`
  line
  line `(v) if it is not packed or labelled as required by or under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(vi) if it is not registered in the manner required by or under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(vii) if the label contains any reference to registration other than the registration number; or`
  line
  line `(viii) if the insecticide has a toxicity which is higher than the level prescribed or is mixed or`
  line `packed with any substance so as to alter its nature or quality or contains any substance which is`
  line `not included in the registration;`
  line
  line `(l) "package" means a box, bottle casket, tin, barrel, case, receptacle, sack, bag, wrapper, or other`
  line `thing in which an insecticide is placed or packed;`
  line
  line `(m) "premises" means any land, shop, stall or place where any insecticide is sold or manufactured`
  line `or stored or used, and includes any vehicle carrying insecticide;`
  line
  line `(n) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "registered", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means registered under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "sale", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means the sale of any`
  line `insecticide, whether for cash or on credit and whether by wholesale or retail, and includes an`
  line `agreement for sale, an offer for sale, the exposing for sale or having in possession for sale of any`
  line `insecticide and includes also an attempt to sell any such insecticide;`
  line
  line `(q) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(r) "worker" means a person employed under a contract of service or apprenticeship.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (1471)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `The Central Insecticides Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1471&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be,`
  line `constitute a Board to be called the, Central Insecticides Board to advise the Central Government and State`
  line `Governments on technical matters arising out of the administration of this Act and to carry out the other`
  line `functions assigned to the Board by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The matters on which the Board may advise under sub-section (1) shall include matters`
  line `relating to--`
  line
  line `(a) the risk to human beings or animals involved in the use of insecticides and the safety`
  line `measures necessary to prevent such risk;`
  line
  line `(b) the manufacture, sale, storage, transport and distribution of insecticides with a view to ensure`
  line `safety to human beings or animals.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the Director General of Heath Services, ex officio, who shall be the Chairman;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Drugs Controller, India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Plant Protection Adviser to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Director of Storage and Inspection, Ministry of Food, Agriculture, Community`
  line `Development and Co-operation (Department of Food), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) the Chief Adviser of Factories, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vi) the Director, National Institute of Communicable Diseases, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(vii) the Director General, Indian Council of Agricultural Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(viii) the Director General, Indian Council of Medical Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ix) the Director, Zoological Survey of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(x) the Director General, Indian Standards Institution, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xi) the Director-General of Shipping or, in his absence, the Deputy Director General of Shipping,`
  line `Ministry of Transport and Shipping, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xii) the Joint Director, Traffic (General), Ministry of Railways (Railway Board), ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xiii) the Secretary, Central Committee for Food Standards, ex officio;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(xiiia) the Animal Husbandry Commissioner, Department of Agriculture, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xiiib) the Joint Commissioner (Fisheries), Department of Agriculture, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xiiic) the Deputy Inspector General of Forests (Wild Life), Department of Agriculture, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(xiiid) the Industrial Adviser (Chemicals), Directorate General of Technical Development,`
  line `ex officio;]`
  line
  line `(xiv) one person to represent the Ministry of Petroleum and Chemicals, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xv) one pharmacologist to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xvi) one medical texicologist to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xvii) one person who shall be in charge of the department dealing with public health in a State, to`
  line `be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xviii) two persons who shall be Directors of Agriculture in States, to be nominated by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(xix) four persons, one of whom shall be an expert in industrial health and occupational hazards,`
  line `to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(xx) one person to represent the Council of Scientific and Industrial Research to be nominated by`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(xxi) one ecologist to be nominated by the Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(4) The persons nominated under clauses (xiv) to ^2`
  line `[(xxi)] inclusive, of sub-section (3) shall, unless`
  line `their seats become vacant earlier by resignation, death or otherwise, hold office for three years from the`
  line `date of their nomination, but shall be eligible for re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that the persons nominated under clauses (xvii) and (xviii) shall hold office only for so long`
  line `as they hold the appointments by virtue of which their nominations were made.`
  line
  line `^3[(5) No act or proceeding of the Board, the Registration Committee or any Committee appointed`
  line `under section 6, shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy in, or`
  line `any defect in the constitution of, the Board, the Registration Committee or such Committee, as the case`
  line `may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for (xx) (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 2, for sub-section (5) (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (1472)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Registration Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1472&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall constitute a Registration Committee`
  line `consisting of a Chairman, and not more than five persons who shall be members of the Board (including`
  line `the Drugs Controller, India and the Plant Protection Adviser to the Government of India)--`
  line
  line `(i) to register insecticides after scrutinising their formulae and verifying claims made by the`
  line `importer or the manufacturer, as the case may be, as regards their efficacy and safety to human beings`
  line `and animals; and`
  line
  line `(ii) to perform such other functions as are assigned to it by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Chairman is not a member of the Board, his term of office and other conditions of`
  line `service shall be such as may be determined by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), a member of the Registration Committee shall hold`
  line `office for so long as he is a member of the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Committee may also co-opt such number of experts and for such purpose or period as it may`
  line `deem fit, but any expert so co-opted shall have no right to vote.`
  line
  line `(5) The Registration Committee shall regulate its own procedure and the conduct of business to be`
  line `transacted by it.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (1473)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Other committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1473&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Board may appoint such committees as it deems fit and may appoint to`
  line `them persons who are not members of the Board, to exercise such powers and perform such duties as`
  line `may, subject to such conditions, if any, as the Board may impose, be delegated to them by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1474)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Procedure for Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1474&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, subject to the previous approval of the Central`
  line `Government, make bye-laws for the purpose of regulating its own procedure and the procedure of any`
  line `committee thereof and the conduct of all business to be transacted by it or such committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1475)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Secretary and other officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1475&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall--`
  line
  line `(i) appoint a person to be the Secretary of the Board who shall also function as Secretary to the`
  line `Registration Committee; and`
  line
  line `(ii) provide the Board and the Registration Committee with such technical and other staff as the`
  line `Central Government considers necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1476)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Registration of insecticides.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1476&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desiring to import or manufacture any insecticide`
  line `may apply to the Registration Committee for the registration of such insecticide and there shall be a`
  line `separate application for each such insecticide:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person engaged in the business of import or manufacture of any insecticide`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this section shall make an application to the Registration`
  line `Committee within a period of^1`
  line `[seventeen months] from the date of such commencement for the`
  line `registration of any insecticide which he has been importing or manufacturing before that date:`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[Provided further that where any person referred to in the preceding proviso fails to make an`
  line `application under that proviso within the period specified therein, he may make such application at any`
  line `time thereafter on payment of a penalty of one hundred rupees for every month or part thereof after the`
  line `expiry of such period for the registration of each such insecticide.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and contain such particulars as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of any such application for the registration of an insecticide, the Committee may, after`
  line `such enquiry as it deems fit and after satisfying itself that the insecticide to which the application relates`
  line `conforms to the claims made by the importer or by the manufacturer, as the case may be, as regards`
  line `the efficacy of the insecticide and its safety to human beings and animals, register ^3`
  line `[on such conditions as`
  line `may be specified by it] and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed, the insecticide, allot a`
  line `registration number thereto and issue a certificate of registration in token thereof within a period of twelve`
  line `months from the date of receipt of the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Committee may, if it is unable within the said period to arrive at a decision on the`
  line `basis of the materials placed before it, extend the period by a further period not exceeding six months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the Committee is of opinion that the precautions claimed by the applicant as`
  line `being sufficient to ensure safety to human beings or animals are not such as can be easily observed or that`
  line `notwithstanding the observance of such precautions the use of the insecticide involves serious risk to`
  line `human beings or animals, it may refuse to register the insecticide.`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(3A) In the case of applications received by it prior to the 31st day of March, 1975, notwithstanding`
  line `the expiry of the period specified in sub-section (3) for the disposal of such applications, it shall be lawful`
  line `and shall be deemed always to have been lawful for the Registration Committee to dispose of such`
  line `applications at any time after such expiry but within a period of one year from the commencement of the`
  line `Insecticides (Amendment) Act, 1977 (24 of 1977):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall be deemed to make any contravention before`
  line `the commencement of the Insecticides (Amendment) Act, 1977 (24 of 1977), of a condition of a`
  line `certificate of registration granted before such commencement, an offence punishable under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3B) Where the Registration Committee is of opinion that the insecticide is being introduced for the`
  line `first time in India, it may, pending any enquiry, register it provisionally for a period of two years on such`
  line `conditions as may be specified by it.`
  line
  line `(3C) The Registration Committee may, having regard to the efficacy of the insecticide and its safety`
  line `to human beings and animals, vary the conditions subject to which a certificate of registration has been`
  line `granted and may for that purpose require the certificate-holder by notice in writing to deliver up the`
  line `certificate to it within such time as may be specified in the notice.]`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where an insecticide has been registered on`
  line `the application of any person, any other person desiring to import or manufacture the insecticide or`
  line `engaged in the business of, import or manufacture thereof shall on application and on payment of`
  line `prescribed fee be allotted a registration number and granted a certificate of registration in respect thereof`
  line `on the same conditions on which the insecticide was originally registered.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1972, s. 2, for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-8-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Proviso ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-8-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 3, for "on such conditions" (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1477)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appeal against non-registration or cancellation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1477&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by a decision of the`
  line `Registration Committee under section 9 may, within a period of thirty days from the date on which the`
  line `decision is communicated to him, appeal in the prescribed manner and on payment of the proscribed fee`
  line `to the Central Government whose decision thereon shall be final:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period, if it`
  line `is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1478)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of revision of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1478&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, at any time, call for`
  line `the record relating to any case in which the Registration committee has given a decision under section 9`
  line `for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the legality or propriety of any such decision and may pass any`
  line `such order in relation thereto as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be passed after the expiry of one year from the date of the decision:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Government shall not pass any order prejudicial to any person unless`
  line `that person has had a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed order.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1479)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Licensing officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1479&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint`
  line `such persons as it thinks fit to be licensing officers for the purposes of this Act and define the areas in`
  line `respect of which they shall exercise jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1480)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Grant of licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1480&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person desiring to manufacture or to sell, stock or exhibit for sale or`
  line `distribute any insecticide ^1`
  line `[or to undertake commercial pest control operations with the use of any`
  line `insecticide], may make an application to the licensing officer for the grant of a licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person engaged in the business of manufacturing or selling, stocking or exhibiting`
  line `for sale or distributing any insecticide immediately before the commencement of this section shall make`
  line `an application to the licensing officer for the grant of a licence within a period of ^2`
  line `[seventeen months]`
  line `from the date of such commencement:`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided further that any person engaged in the commercial pest control operations immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Insecticides (Amendment) Act, 1977 (24 of 1977), shall make an`
  line `application to the licensing officer for the grant of a licence within a period of six months from the`
  line `commencement of the said Act.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form and shall contain such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of any such application for the grant of a licence, the licensing officer may grant a`
  line `licence in such form, on such conditions and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) A licence granted under this section shall be valid for the period specified therein and may be`
  line `renewed from time to time for such period and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a licence has been granted to any person who has made an application`
  line `under ^3`
  line `[the first proviso or, as the case may be, the second proviso] to sub-section (1), that licence shall be`
  line `deemed to be cancelled in relation to any insecticide, the application for registration whereof has been`
  line `refused or the registration whereof has been cancelled, under this Act, with effect from the date on which`
  line `such refusal or cancellation is notified in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `^1[(5) In prescribing fees for the grant or renewal of licences under this section, different fees may be`
  line `prescribed for the sale or distribution of insecticides for purposes of domestic use and for other purposes.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 4 (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1972, s. 3, for "three months" (w.e.f. 1-8-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 4, for "the proviso" (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1481)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Revocation, suspension and amendment of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1481&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the licensing officer is satisfied,`
  line `either on a reference made to him in this behalf or otherwise, that--`
  line
  line `(a) the licence granted under section 13 has been granted because of misrepresentation as to an`
  line `essential fact; or`
  line
  line `(b) the holder of a licence has failed to comply with the conditions subject to which the licence`
  line `was granted or has contravened any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder,`
  line
  line `then, without prejudice to any other penalty to which the holder of the licence may be liable under this`
  line `Act, the licensing officer may, after giving the holder of the licence an opportunity of showing cause,`
  line `revoke or suspend the licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the licensing officer may also vary or amend`
  line `a licence granted under section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1482)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appeal against the decision of a licensing officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1482&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by a decision of a`
  line `licensing officer under section 13 [except under the proviso to sub-section (4)] or section 14 may, within a`
  line `period of thirty days from the date on which the decision is communicated to him, appeal to such`
  line `authority in such manner and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the appellate authority shall, after giving the`
  line `appellant an opportunity of showing cause, dispose of the appeal ordinarily within a period of six months`
  line `and the decision of the appellate authority shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1483)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Central Insecticides Laboratory.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1483&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, establish a Central Insecticides Laboratory under the control of a Director to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government to carry out the functions entrusted to it by or under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government so directs by a notification in the Official Gazette, the`
  line `functions of the Central Insecticides Laboratory shall, to such extent as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, be carried out at any such institution as may be specified therein and thereupon the functions`
  line `of the Director of the Central Insecticides Laboratory shall to the extent so specified be exercised by the`
  line `head of that institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1484)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Prohibition of import and manufacture of certain insecticides.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1972, s. 4, for "under the proviso" (w.e.f. 1-8-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1484&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, himself`
  line `or by any person on his behalf, import or manufacture--`
  line
  line `(a) any misbranded insecticide;`
  line
  line `(b) any insecticide the sale, distribution or use of which is for the time being prohibited under`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(c) any insecticide except in accordance with the conditions on which it was registered;`
  line
  line `(d) any insecticide in contravention of any other provision of this Act or of any rule made`
  line `thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person who has applied for registration of an insecticide ^1`
  line `[under any of the`
  line `provisos] to sub-section (1) of section 9 may continue to import or manufacture any such insecticide and`
  line `such insecticide shall not be deemed to be a misbranded insecticide within the meaning of sub-clause (vi)`
  line `or sub-clause (vii) or sub-clause (viii) of clause (k) of section 3, until he has been informed by the`
  line `Registration Committee of its decision to refuse to register the said insecticide.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall, himself or by any person on his behalf, manufacture any insecticide except under,`
  line `and in accordance with the conditions of, a licence issued for such purpose under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1485)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Prohibition of sale, etc., of certain insecticides.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1485&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, himself or by any person`
  line `on his behalf, sell, stock or exhibit for sale, distribute, ^1`
  line `[transport, use, or cause to be used] by any`
  line worker
  line
  line `(a) any insecticide which is not registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any insecticide, the sale, distribution or use of which is for the time being prohibited under`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(c) any insecticide in contravention of any other provision of this Act or of any rule made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall, himself or by any person on his behalf, sell, stock or exhibit for sale or`
  line `distribute ^2`
  line `[or use for commercial pest control operations] any insecticide except under, and in accordance`
  line `with the conditions of, a licence issued for such purpose under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section an insecticide in respect of which any person has`
  line `applied for a certificate of registration^3`
  line `[under any of the provisos] to sub-section (1) of section 9, shall be`
  line `deemed to be registered till the date on which the refusal to register such insecticide is notified in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 5, for "transport or cause to be used" (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1972, s. 5, for "under the proviso" (w.e.f. 1-8-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1486)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Insecticide Analysts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1486&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or a State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, appoint persons in such number as it thinks fit and possessing such technical and`
  line `other qualifications as may be prescribed to be Insecticide Analysts for such areas and in respect of such`
  line `insecticides or class of insecticides as may be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person who has any financial interest in the manufacture, import or sale of any`
  line `insecticide, shall be so appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1487)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Insecticide Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1487&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or a State Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint persons in such number as it thinks fit and possessing such`
  line `technical and other qualifications as may be prescribed to be Insecticide Inspectors for such areas as may`
  line `be specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person who does not possess the required qualifications may be so appointed only`
  line `for the purposes of clause (a) and clause (d) of sub-section (1) of section 21:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no person who has any financial interest in the manufacture, import or sale of`
  line `any insecticide shall be so appointed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Insecticide Inspector shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), and shall be officially subordinate to such authority as`
  line `the Government appointing him may specify in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1488)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Powers of Insecticide Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1488&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) An Insecticide Inspector shall have power--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter and search, at all reasonable times and with such assistance, if any, as he considers`
  line `necessary, any premises in which he has reason to believe that an offence under this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder has been or is being or is about to be committed, or for the purpose of satisfying`
  line `himself that the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or the conditions of any certificate`
  line `of registration or licence issued thereunder are being complied with;`
  line
  line `(b) to require the production of, and to inspect, examine and make copies of, or take extracts`
  line `from, registers, records or other documents kept by a manufacturer, distributor, carrier, dealer or any`
  line `other person in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder and seize the`
  line `same, if he has reason to believe that all or any of them, may furnish evidence of the commission of`
  line `an offence punishable under this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) to make such examination and inquiry as he thinks fit in order to ascertain whether the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder are being complied with and for that purpose stop`
  line `any vehicle;`
  line
  line `(d) to stop the distribution, sale or use of an insecticide which he has reason to believe is being`
  line `distributed, sold or used in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder,`
  line `for a specified period not exceeding ^1`
  line `[thirty days], or unless the alleged contravention is such that the`
  line `defect may be removed by the possessor of the insecticide, seize the stock of such insecticide;`
  line
  line `(e) to take samples of any insecticide and send such samples for analysis to the Insecticide`
  line `Analyst for test in the prescribed manner; and`
  line
  line `(f) to exercise such other powers as may be necessary for carrying out the purposes of this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to any search or seizure under this Act as they apply to any search or seizure made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under section 94 of the said Code.]`
  line
  line `(3) An Insecticide Inspector may exercise the powers of a police officer under ^3`
  line `[section 42 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], for the purpose of ascertaining the true name and`
  line `residence of the person from whom a sample is taken or an insecticide is seized.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2000, s. 2, for "twenty" (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 6, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "section 57 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)" (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1489)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Procedure to be followed by Insecticide Inspectors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1489&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an Insecticide Inspector seizes`
  line `any record, register or document under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 21, he shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, inform a Magistrate and take his orders as to the custody thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an Insecticide Inspector takes any action under clause (d) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 21--`
  line
  line `(a) he shall use all dispatch in ascertaining whether or not the insecticide or its sale, distribution`
  line `or use contravenes any of the provisions of section 18 and if it is ascertained that the insecticide or its`
  line `sale, distribution or use does not so contravene, forthwith revoke the order passed under the said`
  line `clause or, as the case may be, take such action as may be necessary for the return of the stock seized;`
  line
  line `(b) if he seizes the stock of the insecticide he shall, as soon as may be, inform a Magistrate and`
  line `take his orders as to the custody thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) without prejudice to the institution of any prosecution, if the alleged contravention be such`
  line `that the defect may be remedied by the possessor of the insecticide, he shall, on being satisfied that`
  line `the defect has been so remedied, forthwith revoke his order and in case where the Insecticide`
  line `Inspector has seized the stock of insecticide, he shall, as soon as may be, inform a Magistrate and`
  line `obtain his orders as to the release thereof.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) Where an Insecticide Inspector takes any sample of an insecticide, he shall issue a receipt`
  line `therefor stating therein that the fair price of such sample shall be tendered if the sample, after test or`
  line `analysis is not found to be misbranded and the Insecticide Analyst has reported to that effect and on such`
  line `price having been tendered may require a written acknowledgement therefor.]`
  line
  line `(4)`
  line ^2
  line `*** where the Insecticide Inspector seizes the stock of any insecticide under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 21, he shall tender a receipt therefor in the prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an Insecticide Inspector takes a sample of an insecticide for the purpose of test or analysis,`
  line `he shall intimate such purpose in writing in the prescribed form to the person from whom he takes it and,`
  line `in the presence of such person unless he wilfully absents himself, shall divide the sample into three`
  line `portions and effectively seal and suitably mark the same and permit such person to add his own seal and`
  line `mark to all or any of the portions so sealed and marked:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the insecticide is made up in containers of small volume, instead of dividing a`
  line `sample as aforesaid, the Insecticide Inspector may, and if the insecticide be such that it is likely to`
  line `deteriorate or be otherwise damaged by exposure shall, take three of the said containers after suitably`
  line `marking the same and, where necessary, sealing them.`
  line
  line `(6) The Insecticide Inspector shall restore one portion of a sample so divided or one container, as the`
  line `case may be, to the person from whom he takes it and shall retain the remainder and dispose of the same`
  line `as follows:--`
  line
  line `(i) one portion or container, he shall forthwith send to the Insecticide Analyst for test or`
  line `analysis; and`
  line
  line `(ii) the second, he shall produce to the court before which proceedings, if any, are instituted in`
  line `respect of the insecticide.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2000, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  line
  line `2. The words, brackets and figure Where the price tendered under sub-section (3) is refused, or omitted by s. 3,`
  line `ibid. (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1490)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Persons bound to disclose place where insecticides are manufactured or kept.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1490&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every person`
  line `for the time being in charge of any premises where any insecticide is being manufactured or is kept for`
  line `sale or distribution shall, on being required by an Insecticide Inspector so to do, be legally bound to`
  line `disclose to the Insecticide Inspector the place where the insecticide is being manufactured or is kept, as`
  line `the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1491)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Report of Insecticide Analyst.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1491&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Insecticide Analyst to whom a sample of any`
  line `insecticide has been submitted for test or analysis under sub-section (6) of section 22, shall, within a period of ^1`
  line `[thirty] days, deliver to the Insecticide Inspector submitting it a signed report in duplicate in the`
  line `prescribed form.`
  line
  line `(2) The Insecticide Inspector on receipt thereof shall deliver one copy of the report to the person from`
  line `whom the sample was taken and shall retain the other copy for use in any prosecution in respect of the`
  line sample.
  line
  line `(3) Any document purporting to be a report signed by an Insecticide Analyst shall be evidence of the`
  line `facts stated therein, and such evidence shall be conclusive unless the person from whom the sample was`
  line `taken has within twenty-eight days of the receipt of a copy of the report notified in writing the Insecticide`
  line `Inspector or the court before which any proceedings in respect of the sample are pending that he intends`
  line `to adduce evidence in controversion of the report.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless the sample has already been tested or analysed in the Central Insecticides Laboratory,`
  line `where a person has under sub-section (3) notified his intention of adducing evidence in controversion of`
  line `the Insecticide Analysts report, the court may, of its own motion or in its discretion at the request either`
  line `of the complainant or of the accused, cause the sample of the insecticide produced before the magistrate`
  line `under sub-section (6) of section 22 to be sent for test or analysis to the said laboratory, ^2`
  line `[which shall,`
  line `within a period of thirty days, make the test or analysis] and report in writing signed by, or under the`
  line `authority of, the Director of the Central Insecticides Laboratory the result thereof, and such report shall be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the facts stated therein.`
  line
  line `(5) The cost of a test or analysis made by the Central Insecticides Laboratory under sub-section (4)`
  line `shall be paid by the complainant or the accused, as the court shall direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2000, s. 4, for "sixty" (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "which shall make the test or analysis" (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1492)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title Confiscation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1492&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person has been convicted under this Act for contravening any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act or of the rules made thereunder, the stock of the insecticide in respect of which`
  line `the contravention has been made shall be liable to confiscation.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), where the Court is satisfied on`
  line `the application of an Insecticide Inspector or otherwise and after such inquiry as may be necessary, that`
  line `the insecticide is a misbranded insecticide, such insecticide shall be liable to confiscation.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1493)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Notification of poisoning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1493&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `require any person or class of persons specified therein to report all occurrences of poisoning (through the`
  line `use or handling of any insecticide) coming within his or their cognizance to such officer as may be`
  line `specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1494)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Prohibition of sale, etc., of insecticides for reasons of public safety.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. The words, brackets and figure sub-clause (iii) of omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1494&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on receipt of a`
  line `report under section 26 or otherwise, the Central Government or the State Government is of opinion for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, that the use of any insecticide specified in ^1`
  line `*** clause (e) of section 3`
  line `or any specific batch thereof is likely to involve such risk to human beings or animals as to render it`
  line `expedient or necessary to take immediate action then that Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, prohibit the sale, distribution or use of the insecticide or batch, in such area, to such extent and`
  line `for such period (not exceeding sixty days) as may be specified in the notification pending investigation`
  line `into the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the investigation is not completed within the said period, the Central Government`
  line `or the State Government, as the case may be, may extend it by such further period or periods not`
  line `exceeding thirty days in the aggregate as it may specify in a like manner.`
  line
  line `(2) If, as a result of its own investigation or on receipt of the report from the State Government, and`
  line `after consultation with the Registration Committee, the Central Government, is satisfied that the use of`
  line `the said insecticide or batch is or is not likely to cause any such risk, it may pass such order (including an`
  line `order refusing to register the insecticide or cancelling the certificate of registration, if any, granted in`
  line `respect thereof) as it deems fit, depending on the circumstances of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1495)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Notification of cancellation of registration, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1495&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `A refusal to register any insecticide or a`
  line `cancellation of the certificate of registration of any insecticide shall be notified in the Official Gazette and`
  line `in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1496)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences and punishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1496&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever,--`
  line
  line `(a) imports, manufactures, sells, stocks or exhibits for sale or distributes any insecticide deemed`
  line `to be misbranded under sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (iii) or sub-clause (viii) of clause (k) of`
  line `section 3; or`
  line
  line `(b) imports or manufactures any insecticide without a certificate of registration; or`
  line
  line `(c) manufactures, sells, stocks or exhibits for sale or distributes an insecticide without a`
  line `licence; or`
  line
  line `(d) sells or distributes an insecticide, in contravention of section 27; or`
  line
  line `(e) causes an insecticides, the use of which has been prohibited under section 27, to be used by`
  line `any worker; or`
  line
  line `(f) obstructs an Insecticide Inspector in the exercise of his powers or discharge of his duties under`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder,`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[shall be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) for the first offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to fifty thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the second and a subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years, or with fine which shall not be less than fifteen thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `seventy-five thousand rupees, or with both.]`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever uses an insecticide in contravention of any provision of this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder shall be punishable with fine ^2`
  line `[which shall not be less than five hundred rupees but which may`
  line `extend to five thousand rupees, or imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with`
  line both.]
  line
  line `(3) Whoever contravenes any of the other provisions of this Act or any rule made thereunder or any`
  line `condition of a certificate of registration or licence granted thereunder, shall be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) for the first offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^3`
  line `[one year, or with`
  line `fine which shall not be less than five thousand rupees but which may extend to twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees, or with both`
  line
  line `(ii) for the second and a subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line ^4
  line `[two years, or with fine which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to`
  line `fifty thousand rupees, or with both.]`
  line
  line `(4) If any person convicted of an offence under this Act commits a like offence afterwards it shall be`
  line `lawful for the court before which the second or subsequent conviction takes place to cause the offenders`
  line `name and place of residence, the offence and the penalty imposed to be published in such newspapers or`
  line `in such other manner as the court may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2000, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "which may extend to five hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "six months, or with fine, or with both" (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "one year, or with fine, or with both" (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1497)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Defences which may or may not be allowed in prosecutions under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1497&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as`
  line `hereinafter provided in this section, it shall be no defence in a prosecution under this Act to prove merely`
  line `that the accused was ignorant of the nature or quality of the insecticide in respect of which the offence`
  line `was committed or of the risk involved in the manufacture, sale or use of such insecticide or of the`
  line `circumstances of its manufacture or import.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of section 17, an insecticide shall not be deemed to be misbranded only by`
  line `reason of the fact that--`
  line
  line `(a) there has been added thereto some innocuous substance or ingredient because the same is`
  line `required for the manufacture or the preparation of the insecticide as an article of commerce in a state`
  line `fit for carriage or consumption, and not to increase the bulk, weight or measure of the insecticide or to`
  line `conceal its inferior quality or other defect; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the process of manufacture, preparation or conveyance some extraneous substance has`
  line `unavoidably become intermixed with it.`
  line
  line `(3) A person not being an importer or a manufacturer of an insecticide or his agent for the distribution`
  line `thereof, shall not be liable for a contravention of any provision of this Act, if he proves--`
  line
  line `(a) that he acquired the insecticide from an importer or a duly licensed manufacturer, distributor`
  line `or dealer thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) that he did not know and could not, with reasonable diligence, have ascertained that the`
  line `insecticide in any way contravened any provision of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) that the insecticide, while in his possession, was properly stored and remained in the same`
  line `state as when he acquired it.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1498)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Cognizance and trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 24 of 1977, s. 7, for "presidency magistrate or a magistrate of the first class" (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1498&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) No prosecution for an offence under this Act shall be`
  line `instituted except by, or with the written consent of, the State Government or a person authorised in this`
  line `behalf by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a ^1`
  line `[metropolitan magistrate or a judicial magistrate of the first class]`
  line `shall try any offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (1499)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 32
  title `Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2000, s. 7 (w.e.f. 5-8-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1499&sectionno=31A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[31A. Special Courts.--(1) If the State Government is satisfied that it is necessary for the purpose`
  line `of providing for speedy trial of offences under this Act in any district or metropolitan area, it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette and after consultation with the High Court, notify one or more Courts`
  line `of Judicial Magistrates of the first class, or, as the case may be, Metropolitan Magistrates, in such district`
  line `or metropolitan area to be Special Courts for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise directed by the High Court, a court notified under sub-section (1) shall exercise`
  line `jurisdiction only in respect of cases under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), the jurisdiction and powers of the presiding officer of`
  line `court notified under sub-section (1) in any district or metropolitan area shall extend throughout the district`
  line `or the metropolitan area, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section, a court notified under sub-section (1) in any`
  line `district or metropolitan area shall be deemed to be a court established under sub-section (1) of section 11,`
  line `or, as the case may be, sub-section (1) of section 16 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)`
  line `and the provisions of that Code shall apply accordingly in relation to such courts.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section, "High Court" has the same meaning as in clause (e) of section 2 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1506)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1506&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `[Magistrate's power to impose enhanced penalties.] Omitted by the Insecticides (Repealing and`
  line `Amending) Act 1977 (24 of 1977), s. 8 (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (1507)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1507&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, or was responsible`
  line `to the company for the conduct of the business of, the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he`
  line `exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section:--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (1508)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1508&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions to any State Government as may appear to the Central Government to be necessary for carrying`
  line `into execution in the State any of the provisions of this Act or of any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (1509)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1509&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution, suit or other proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Government or any officer of the Government or the Board, the Registration Committee or`
  line `any Committee of the Board, for anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (1510)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1510&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after`
  line `consultation with the Board and subject to the condition of previous publication, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that consultation with the Board may be dispensed with if the Central Government is of`
  line `opinion that circumstances have arisen which render it necessary to make rules without such consultation`
  line `but in such a case the Board shall be consulted within six months of the making of the rules and the`
  line `Central Government shall take into consideration any suggestions which the Board may make in relation`
  line `to the amendment of the said rules.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line prescribe--
  line
  line `(a) the method of packing and labelling;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of registration of an insecticide;`
  line
  line `(c) the functions of the Board and of the Registration Committee and the travelling and other`
  line `allowances payable to members of the Board, the Registration Committee and any Committee of the`
  line Board;
  line
  line `(d) the places at which insecticides may be imported and prohibit their import at any other place;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of application for registration of an insecticide and the particulars relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(f)`
  line ^1
  line `* * * the fee payable in respect of registration;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of appeal to the Central Government under section 10 and the fee payable`
  line therefore;
  line
  line `(h) the form of application for the grant of licence and the particulars relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of licence, the conditions attached thereto and the fee payable therefore;`
  line
  line `(j) the period for which a licence may be renewed and the fee for such renewal;`
  line
  line `(k) the circumstances in which a licence may be varied or amended under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(l) the functions of the Central Insecticides Laboratory;`
  line
  line `(m) the qualifications, powers and duties of an Insecticide Analyst and an Insecticide Inspector;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner of testing or analysing the samples of any insecticide and the fee payable therefor;`
  line
  line `(o) the form in which intimation shall be given by an Insecticide Inspector under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 22 to a person from whom a sample of an insecticide is taken for test or analysis;`
  line
  line `(p) the form in which an Insecticide Analyst shall submit a report of his test or analysis to the`
  line `Insecticide Inspector under sub-section (1) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(q) the protective clothing and equipment to be used by workers during the manufacture,`
  line `formulation, transport, distribution and application of insecticides and other facilities to be provided`
  line `to keep themselves and things supplied to them free from any contamination;`
  line
  line `(r) the use by the workers of any such protective clothing, equipment and other facilities;`
  line
  line `(s) the precautions to be taken against poisoning through the use or handling of insecticides;`
  line
  line `(t) the measures for detecting and investigating cases in which poisoning has occurred;`
  line
  line `(u) the facilities to be provided for ensuring first-aid treatment;`
  line
  line `(v) the instruction and training to be provided regarding the use of things supplied to the workers`
  line `for ensuring their safety;`
  line
  line `(w) the facilities for medical examination of workers engaged in the manufacture or handling of`
  line insecticides;
  line
  line ^2
  line `* * * * *`
  line
  line `(y) the equipment for, and method of, application of, an insecticide and the disposal of surplus`
  line `material, washings and containers, following application;`
  line
  line `(z) the maintenance and inspection of records and returns;`
  line
  line `(za) the restrictions on storage of insecticides during transport or, otherwise along with articles of`
  line food;
  line
  line `(zb) the maximum proportion of any insecticide which may be added to, or contained in, any`
  line `preparation for domestic use and the restrictions thereon;`
  line
  line `(zc) the manner in which refusal to register an insecticide or cancellation of certificate of`
  line `registration thereof may be notified;`
  line
  line `(zd) the officer or authority to whom the Central Government may delegate any of the powers and`
  line `functions conferred on it by this Act;`
  line
  line `(ze) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session ^3`
  line `[or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "the conditions of registration and" omitted by Act 24 of 1977, s. 9 (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (x) omitted by Act 24 of 1977, s. 9 (w.e.f. 2-8-1977).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 2-8-1977)`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (1511)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power of the State Governments to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1511&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, after`
  line `consultation with the board and subject to the condition of previous publication, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act and not`
  line `inconsistent with the rules, if any, made by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority to which, the manner in which, and the fee on payment of which, an appeal may`
  line `be filed under section 15 and the procedure to be followed by the appellate authority in disposing of`
  line `the appeal;`
  line
  line `(b) the delegation of any of the powers and functions conferred by this Act on the State`
  line `Government to any officer or authority specified by that Government.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before the State Legislature.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (1512)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title Exemption.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487&sectionId=1512&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_31_00001_196846_1517807318487
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing in this Act shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the use of any insecticide by any person for his own household purposes or for kitchen garden`
  line `or in respect of any land under his cultivation;`
  line
  line `(b) any substance specified or included in the Schedule or any preparation containing any one or`
  line `more such substances, if such substance or preparation is intended for purposes other than preventing,`
  line `destroying, repelling or mitigating any insects, rodents, fungi, weeds and other forms of plant or`
  line `animal life not useful to human beings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, and subject to such`
  line `conditions, if any, as it may specify therein, exempt from all or any of the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `rules made thereunder, any educational, scientific or research organisation engaged in carrying out`
  line `experiments with insecticides.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
